本論文永久網址:      Twitter研究生:李姿青研究生(外文):Li Tzu Ching論文名稱:員工自我效能、學習策略與數位學習成效關係之研究論文名稱(外文):A Study of the relationship of employee self-efficacy,learning strategy and e-learning effectiveness指導教授:黃佳純指導教授(外文):王湧泉博士學位類別:碩士校院名稱:國立高雄應用科技大學系所名稱:人力資源發展系碩士班學門:商業及管理學門學類:其他商業及管理學類論文出版年:2007畢業學年度:95語文別:中文論文頁數:105中文關鍵詞:數位學習、自我效能、學習策略、數位學習成效外文關鍵詞:e-Learning self-efficacy learning strategy e-Learning effectiveness、taiwan相關次數:

被引用:61點閱:1422評分:下載:470書目收藏:5



在網際網路的普及與節省教育訓練成本的考量下，愈來愈多的企業使用數位學習(e-Learning)來進行員工的教育訓練。台灣企業近年來也逐漸投入數位學習市場，且企業規模與數位學習導入率呈正比，企業規模愈大，導入數位學習的意願就愈高。在資策會2006年之《大型企業導入數位學習調查報告》中發現，企業投入數位學習金額，已由2005年的1億600萬元，上升到2006年的近3億元，成長1.8倍。隨著企業導入數位學習的增加，數位學習的成效也愈形重要，過去有關數位學習成效探討主要是著重在個人特質、學習動機、電腦態度對數位學習成效的影響，而員工本身的自我效能及員工採用的學習策略對於數位學習成效的影響則較少被提及。故本研究主要目的在探討員工自我效能、學習策略對數位學習成效的影響，亦進一步探索自我效能與學習策略間關聯性。本研究是以國內有使用數位學習的企業員工為研究對象，研究共發出350份問捲，回收有效樣本278份。經實證分析結果顯示，自我效能和學習成效有關，即自我效能愈高的員工，其學習成效也愈高。學習策略和學習成效有關，即員工在進行數位學習時，若能藉由學習策略來幫助學習，其學習成效也愈高。最後，自我效能和學習策略有關，即自我效能愈高的員工，愈會使用學習策略來幫助自己學習。

More and more business use e-Learning in employee training due to the popularity of internet and the consideration of cost reduction. Recently, businesses in Taiwan increasingly start to join the e-Learning market. And the implementation rate of e-Learning in business is proportional to business scale. The larger the business, the more willingness to implement e-Learning. According to “The 2006 Survey Report of E-Learning Implementation in Large Scale Business from Institute for Information Industry”, the amount of money business spent in e-Learning raised from 106 million in 2005 to 300 million in2006, which represents a 1.8 times of growth. Accompanying with the growth of e-Learning implementation in business, e-Learning effectiveness becomes more crucial. In the past researchers paid more attention to the impacts of personality、motivation、comptuer attitudes on e-Learning effectiveness. Fewer attempts have been put to investigate the impacts of employee’s self-efficacy and learning strategies on e-Learning effectiveness. Therefore, the purpose of this study was to investigate the impacts of employee’s self-efficacy and learning strategies on e-Learning effectiveness. And the relationship between self-efficacy and learning strategies was explored. The subject of this study was the employees from business organization in which e-Leaning was implemented. A total of 350 questionnaires were sent out, and 278 effective ones were received. According to the result achieved the conclusions:There was significant correlation between self-efficacy and e-Learning effectiveness. When employees had higher self-efficacy, they were more satified with e-Learning. There was significant correlation between learning strategies and e-Learning effectiveness. When employees used learning strategies to help them learn, they were more satified with e-Learning. Finally, there was significant correlation between self-efficacy and learning strategies. When employees had higher self-efficacy, they used more learning strategy to help them learn.

